<dl id="n54145e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54145e">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54145e"> 145(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> patrilinear <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54145e"><li>FW 279.04 </li><li><a href="../../flex/lf/lexlf.htm#n54145e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/lf/l39lf.htm#n54145e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54145e">MS BL 47478-339</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:318 <a name="lad13" href="../../ff/fdra/lda.htm#lfd4">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/lf/lfd4.htm#n54145e">Draft: II.2&sect;7.4</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&laquo;Dans la r&eacute;gion de Kimberley et dans les autres o&ugrave; j&apos;ai travaill&eacute;, le p&egrave;re est &eacute;troitement associ&eacute; avec la horde locale et ses totems, et par cons&eacute;quent la descendance <mark>patrilin&eacute;aire</mark> et la descendance locale reviennent &agrave; peu pr&egrave;s au m&ecirc;me ; pourtant, comme je l&apos;ai d&eacute;j&agrave; dit, le principe local, avec ses associations (participations) spirituelles, sacr&eacute;es, et mythologiques, semble bien &ecirc;tre primordial, et le plus fondamental des deux.&raquo; <br><font color="green">["In the Kimberley area and the others where I have worked, the father is closely associated with the local horde and its totems, and therefore the patrilineal descent and the local descent are more or less the same; however, as I said before, the local principle, with its spiritual, sacred, and mythological associations (participations), seems to be paramount, and the more fundamental of the two."]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 184</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: A patriline is a person&apos;s father, and additional ancestors, as traced only through males. </mm> </dd></dl>
